content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 393.9 - Accident occurring before july 1, 1939

State Regulations

In the case of an accident occurring before July 1, 1939, the insurance carrier shall not be entitled to a refund in the event of the
death of a claimant after the commuted amount has been paid into the aggregate
trust fund, nor shall the carrier receive any credit for the amount paid in on
a disability case if death results from the accident subsequently and an award
is made for death benefits. Notes
